Package: AHM
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian DINA Estimation with Unknown Attribute Hierarchy
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-06-23
Authors@R: person("Xue", "Wang", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "wangx625@nenu.edu.cn")
Author: Xue Wang [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Xue Wang <wangx625@nenu.edu.cn>
Description: Implements Bayesian estimation via MCMC for the DINA model
    with an unknown attribute hierarchy, allowing the Q-matrix to be either
    unknown and estimated jointly or supplied as known. The package estimates item
    slipping and guessing parameters,
    examinee attribute profiles, latent class probabilities, the attribute
    hierarchy, and the Q-matrix when it is treated as unknown. It also includes post-processing for
    attribute
    label switching, Gelman-Rubin Rhat diagnostics, DIC-based chain selection,
    posterior point estimates, simulation utilities, and a bundled ECPE
    real-data example originally distributed with the CDM package.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
